Class ClassStaticContext

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.usi.dag.disl.staticcontext.AbstractStaticContext
      • ch.usi.dag.disl.staticcontext.ClassStaticContext
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    StaticContext

    public class ClassStaticContext
extends AbstractStaticContext
    Provides class related static context information for the method being instrumented.

      All Methods Instance Methods Concrete Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      java.lang.String getInternalName()
      Returns the internal name of the instrumented class, i.e., a fully qualified class name, with packages delimited by the '/' character.
      java.lang.String getName()
      Returns the type name of the instrumented class, i.e., a fully qualified class name, with packages delimited by the '.' character.
      java.lang.String getOuterClassInternalName()
      Returns the internal name of the class enclosing the instrumented class, or null if the instrumented class is not enclosed in another class.
      java.lang.String getOuterMethodDescriptor()
      Returns outer method descriptor of the instrumented class.
      java.lang.String getOuterMethodName()
      Returns the name of the method enclosing the instrumented class, or null if the class is not enclosed in a method.
      java.lang.String getSignature()
      Returns the signature of the instrumented class, or null if the class is not a generic type.
      java.lang.String getSimpleName()
      Returns the simple name of the instrumented class, i.e., a class name without the package part of the name.
      java.lang.String getSourceFile()
      Returns the name of the source file containing the instrumented class.
      java.lang.String getSuperClassInternalName()
      Returns the internal name of the super class of the instrumented class, i.e., a fully qualified class name, with package names delimited by the '/' character.
      int getVersion()
      Returns class version as (ASM) integer of the instrumented class.
      boolean isAbstract()
      Returns true if the instrumented class is abstract.
      boolean isAnnotation()
      Returns true if the instrumented class is an annotation.
      boolean isEnum()
      Returns true if the instrumented class is an enum.
      boolean isFinal()
      Returns true if the instrumented class is final.
      boolean isInterface()
      Returns true if the instrumented class is an interface.
      boolean isPrivate()
      Returns true if the instrumented class is private.
      boolean isProtected()
      Returns true if the instrumented class is protected.
      boolean isPublic()
      Returns true if the instrumented class is public.
      boolean isSynthetic()
      Returns true if the instrumented class is synthetic.
